radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is enlarged at 9 mm with wall hyperenhancement and surrounding mild fat stranding. The liver has scattered hypodensities too small to characterize, with no ascites. Pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, and urinary bladder appear normal. No evidence of perforation or appendicolith. Eccentric enhancement of the right lateral prostate noted. No lymphadenopathy or free fluid in the pelvis.
